# Rule 110 - Backend

## Boundaries

- Domain types live under `modules/<feature>/domain/`.
- Application use-cases under `modules/<feature>/application/`.
- Infrastructure (DB, HTTP, queue) under `modules/<feature>/infrastructure/`.
- UI-facing code never imports from `infrastructure/` directly; it goes via `application/`.

## Validation

- Every external input has a schema (Zod / valibot / ajv).
- Reject early, reject loudly, log the correlation id.

## Errors

- Domain errors are typed. HTTP errors live at the boundary.
- Never swallow errors. `catch { /* ignore */ }` requires a comment justifying why.

## Data

- Migrations are forward-only. Rollbacks are ADR-triggered.
- Seed scripts are idempotent.
- No raw SQL outside `repository/` layer.

## Observability

- Structured logs (JSON), one event per meaningful state change.
- Correlation id on every request, propagated through async work.

## Security

- Input validation at the boundary.
- Output encoding at the boundary.
- No PII in logs.
- Secrets only via env, never hardcoded.
